FAMILY IS EVERYTHING!

Raising kids isn't easy

CLICK THE LINK IN BIO TO WATCH/LISTEN!
Supernanny's Parenting Secrets - w/ @jofrost 

Even if you don’t have children, having a strong relationship is not easy…

We cover both of these things in the interview… Obviously we talk a great deal about raising children. But we also discussed relationships in general, that don’t involve children 

As parents, building a STRONG and HEALTHY family is the most rewarding thing we’ll ever do in our lives. This week's guest Jo Frost is the world's top expert in this department!

She became a fixture in England where she was the central figure in the popular television show Supernanny UK. In fact, spinoffs were created in almost 50 countries, cementing Jo’s reputation as a family, relationships, and parenting expert.  Since that time, she has done other television work and wrote several books on improving family dynamics and raising children as well.

In our interview, Jo lays out the challenges of how the world has become and a pressure-filled place to raise a family, especially in a post-pandemic era. Technology and social media have also further complicated and impacted our lives as well

Despite these changes, Jo has takeaways on how family dynamics have not changed in many ways. The need to create a STABLE and LOVING home is as timeless as ever. That provides children with the courage they need to go out and live their best lives, knowing they will always have a SAFE SANCTUARY waiting for them.

We also dig into the proper way to DISCIPLINE children, how to create family goals, and navigate through difficult issues in families where dysfunction exists.

She is on point when we talk about CONFIDENCE, having a plan, why it’s important to let children fail, and how parents should react when failure does take place.

If you're looking to improve your FAMILY DYNAMICS and RELATIONSHIPS, you must listen to this podcast.

First , let me just tell you upfront…THIS IS A TRULY INCREDIBLE CONVERSATION!

CLICK THE LINK IN BIO TO WATCH/LISTEN!! ⁣⁣
Unrivaled Clemson Culture - w/ Dabo Swinney from @clemsonfb 

This is a Master Class on LEADERSHIP, FAITH, CULTURE and LIFE

Even if you are only a casual follower of college football, you’re undoubtedly familiar with Clemson Tigers head coach Dabo Swinney. 

Over the past three decades few coaches can rival the SUCCESS Coach Swinney has enjoyed.

You learn a lot about LIFE and what it takes to succeed as a player and a coach in college football. And Coach Swinney learned a long time ago about what it takes to be a WINNER.

He became Clemson's head coach in 2009 and has built an ASTONISHING legacy since that time.  Coach Swinney’s teams have won 81% of their games going 140-33.  He also led the Tigers to national championships in 2016 and 2018.  And for the past three seasons, he’s coached Trevor Lawrence, who many consider the finest quarterback coming out of college football in quite a long time.

To enjoy such a high level of success for an extended period you must have STANDARDS and a CULTURE in place that let's players EXCEL to their HIGHEST CAPACITY. Coach Sweeney talks about what that culture is and how Clemson’s culture actually turned into a brand that has made it easier to continue to RECRUIT THE BEST TALENT in the nation.

Coach Swinney is also a man of FAITH. And he has infused his coaching style and his relationship with his players with faith-based principles that have also significantly contributed to the positive culture at Clemson.

One of the best ways you can learn to be SUCCESSFUL in your own life is to learn from others who have enjoyed the highest levels of success in their life and in the teams they coach.

Coach Swinney goes way beyond the Xs and Os to deliver an INSPIRING and INSIGHTFUL exchange of ideas that you will not want to miss.

You want to know what it’s like to train MICHAEL JORDAN and KOBE BRYANT?  You want to know what sets them and other next-level performers apart from high achievers with just as many gifts and talents? 

Tim Grover has the ANSWERS. 

Tim founded ATTACK Athletics, Inc. in 1989 and since that time, he has worked with hundreds of NFL, MLB, NBA, and Olympic athletes including Michael Jordan and Kobe Bryant. Tim is one of my oldest and dearest friends so it was easy to get him to talk about the nature of FAME, what it takes to be the absolute best, GRIT VS. GLAMOUR, and why it’s not necessarily easy when you do reach the top.

Tim is also uniquely qualified to tell stories about how Kobe lived his life and what you can take from his MAMBA MENTALITY.

Straight up, this is HONEST talk from the best in the business.

This week's show is special 

CLICK THE LINK IN BIO TO WATCH/LISTEN!! ⁣⁣
Reflections on Turning 50 - w/ @edmylett 

I was blessed to celebrate my 50th birthday last week with several close friends and family members.  THANK YOU to every one of you in my extended family who sent me kind wishes as well.

This was a big one for me and got me thinking back to the people and events that have shaped my life and INSPIRED me over the years.  I’ve told stories about these things before, but I wanted to share some of them with you again, not only because they mean a lot to me, but because I think you’ll get a lot out of them too.

On the show this week, Im honored to share some of my favorites with you .

I hope they inspire you, and make a huge impact on your life as they did on mine

I love telling the funny story about a little kid named Ray Ray and what he taught me about standing up for myself.  I also want you to hear how my first job after college taking care of a bunch of boys in a group foster home changed my life forever.

I’ve also pulled out a couple of stories that will tell you why HELPING YOU is so important to me and why I want you to break through the things that limit you so that you can lead a BLISSFUL life, too.

Most of all, I want you to know my dad better and the example he set by quietly SERVING and HELPING others after conquering alcoholism. 

Even though he passed earlier this year, the impacts he had on me and everyone he reached out to are going to echo for ETERNITY. 

I miss him every day.

ENJOY this weeks episode!

Discover how your inner energy works!

CLICK THE LINK IN BIO TO WATCH/LISTEN!! ⁣⁣
Life, Death, and Energy - w/ @psychicmediumje 

John Edward is one of the country’s most renowned psychic mediums. For three decades, he has helped thousands of people with his uncanny ability to predict future events and communicate with those who have crossed over to the Other Side. He is the author of several critically-acclaimed New York Times Best Sellers, AND the star of the hit TV show - Crossing Over with John Edward. 

You don't have to believe that certain people may have a greater power of intuition or discernment, in order to benefit from this interview. Bluntly, you don’t have to believe in psychics to benefit from this conversation.

In fact, I consulted with some of my dearest Christian pastor friends before I even had John on the show to get their opinion, and each of them encouraged me strongly to have this conversation. And I’m glad that I did.

I’ll tell you this… You’re going to be riveted!

At some point, every single one of us will experience the loss of a loved one and the grief that comes along with it. It is an inevitable fact of life. My conversation with John will offer a new perspective on life, death, and the energy that surrounds us. 

In this wide-ranging interview, John and I get into a detailed explanation of the vibrational energy we use to create perceptions that guide us in the world, how we can inventory the energy we have and need, and how we use this same energy to manifest our futures.

We delve into why people are so fascinated with death as the great unknown and why John believes the real grieving over the loss of a loved one takes place the second year after they’ve passed.

John's profession comes with a great deal of skepticism and criticism... similar to the naysayers your encounter in your own life. John and I get real about how he deals with the negativity AND how you can block out the noise and find success NO MATTER WHAT the haters say!

Somebody’s got to be the best… why not YOU?

Championship Mindset of a UFC Fighter - w/ @mikechandlermma 

Michael Chandler is a UFC Top Competitor, and a person you can aspire to be like both in and out of the Octagon. He’s a 3x Bellator Lightweight Champion and is on his way to holding the UFC Lightweight title. He is a rising star, a good friend of mine, and truly one of the greats! 

When you are locked in a cage staring in the face of an opponent that wants to rip your head off, it becomes just as much of a mental game as it is a physical one. 

In this episode, Michael shares his secrets to preparing his mind for a WIN, eliminating the fear of failure, embracing failure, and being able to step fully into his purpose and his greatness! 

No matter where you came from or how much of a slump you might be in, it’s time for you to THINK DIFFERENTLY! Michael went 688 days in between wins before he became an “overnight success.” It was all about his mental ability to overcome imposter syndrome, and embrace his past while FIGHTING for his future… for who he was destined to become! 

The strategies you’ll learn in this interview will help you to accept your God-given imperfections and break free from the jail of self-doubt, how to create a mental highlight reel, and prepare your mind to win your next BIG FIGHT! 

This is NOT just a SPORTS interview! It’s a master class on mental preparation, visualization and changing your mindset… I’m not exaggerating when I called a master class!

Don’t miss Michael’s next BIG FIGHT. It’s the main event on PPV May 15th against Charles Oliveira.

I wanna talk about MENTAL HEALTH today.

We don't talk enough about it, because I think there is often shame attached to it, when we struggle with it

Let me be the first to tell you that it’s something I’ve struggled with all of my life

It may surprise you to hear that

But, it’s true

And you know what?

I think it’s pretty normal

I think most of us have ups and downs mentally and emotionally… I believe it’s part of being human

Yet when it happens to us, we think it’s completely abnormal and there’s something wrong with us and we should be ashamed of it

It’s interesting because when we struggle with our physical health, we’re not ashamed? Are we?

There are definitely many degrees of mental health issues. Different levels of severity, ranging from everything from basic worry and anxiety, all the way to very serious clinical depression

There is a very broad spectrum and there is not a one size fits all solution 

Nonetheless, most of us struggle with it at least a little bit, if we’re being honest

For me, it’s usually moderate depression, feelings of some sadness (when I really shouldn’t be), some anxiety and some worry mixed in

I wouldn’t say my issues are severe… But they certainly exist

And that’s why I’ve been so vigilant in my life about learning the tools to live a better, more productive and blissful life…

And that’s why I work so hard to help you with yours

Your brain is an INCREDIBLE product of GOD’S WORK, but it also needs time to BREATHE every now and again. That’s when it devotes time and energy to process, file away, and work on solutions for everything in your life

INVEST in yourself and your MENTAL HEALTH by meditating or praying, going for a walk, watching the sunset, hitting the gym, curling up with a good book, spending time on your favorite hobby, or simply sitting outside and getting some afternoon sunshine and fresh air.

MOVE your BODY…

HYDRATE

If it’s severe enough

TALK TO SOMEONE ABOUT IT

You are NOT ALONE .

You deserve PEACE 

I promise you I will be here for you in anyway that I possibly can

Many others will be there for you as well

God bless you.

Please, SHARE with those that need to hear this today..

The biggest battles you'll ever FIGHT are the ones that go on between your ears.

Your mind is your most valuable ASSET but it is also where countless thoughts constantly compete with each other for your ATTENTION. Some of those thoughts are positive, and others are not. Sorting through them isn't easy, and sometimes you can get lost or overwhelmed.

How you react to these conflicts sets the tone for your life.

The first step to GREATNESS is believing that you can WIN those battles, time and time again, so that you can create your personal path to SUCCESS.

Can you be HONEST when it comes to assessing both your shortcomings and your STRENGTHS AND GIFTS?

Can you get to a place in your life where are you truly believe you're WORTHY of success? Do you have an understanding of what it takes to reach this plateau?

If not, you’ll need to dig deep and CHALLENGE yourself to do the hard work of finding answers and changing how you think about yourself.

Faith moves mountains, and for you to achieve success you have to have FAITH in yourself and BELIEVE you can do the difficult things that will give you the success you want.

If you want to lead people EFFECTIVELY, you have to wire them to WIN.

You can apply this idea in any situation whether it's as the head of your family, as the coach of a sports team, or the owner of a large business.

You WIRE PEOPLE TO WIN by identifying their unique GIFTS and TALENTS.

You must be very specific. Spend as much time as it takes to uncover these things. LISTEN and OBSERVE so that you can zero in on exactly what makes them SPECIAL.

Some people might be great at public speaking. Others may be an awesome salesman, a straight A student, a star athlete, or even something as simple as a great listener.

Many people instinctively know what gifts they have but often haven't had any CONFIRMATION by somebody else. As a result, these gifts aren’t always utilized to their MAXIMUM BENEFIT.

After you've identified these traits, you need to find places where those people and those gifts can EXCEL.

Getting people to buy in and BELIEVE they can use these gifts as a way to win not only serves them well, it also helps you accomplish your goals as a leader.

SHARE THIS POST with a friend, parent, or business partner who needs to read this!

node.text:
No one is immune to making mistakes. But how we respond afterward makes all the difference.
⁣
I can guarantee you that there’s not one person living on this earth that doesn’t have something to be sorry for.
⁣
Maybe it’s the way you treated someone...⁣
⁣
Maybe it’s a circumstance that was out of your control...⁣
⁣
Maybe you saw something but didn’t say something...⁣
⁣
Maybe you did the best that you could at the time and things just didn’t work out the way you expected...⁣
⁣
 I want to remind you that it’s not enough to just apologize or feel remorse. The best apology is changed behavior.⁣
It’s how we grow. It’s how we evolve.⁣
⁣
That means you must actually DO something!
⁣
If you hurt someone, DO SOMETHING to make it right or at least prove you give a damn. And if you don’t have that opportunity, make a change in YOURSELF so that you never treat another person like that again.
⁣
There are many circumstances in the world right now that you may have not created and seem to be out of your control, but you can still TAKE ACTION within your immediate circle and be a part of the solution!⁣
⁣
And the next time you see something that you know in your heart is wrong, remember this message and SPEAK UP for those who may not have a voice for themselves.
⁣
And this works the same way for people who have wronged YOU! You can tell the sincerity of an apology by the way they behave.
⁣
Has their behavior changed or were they just giving you lip service?⁣
⁣
I challenge you to stop TALKING about it and BE about it!
⁣

Is it possible to push past the human body’s PERCEIVED LIMITATIONS and do what no person has ever done before?

In a word, YES!

And James Lawrence, the IRON COWBOY, is the man who has done just that.

I think we can all agree that completing a single IRON MAN TRIATHLON by itself is an INCREDIBLE athletic feat. However, lots of people have accomplished it, so James set a much loftier goal: 50 Ironmans, 50 states, and on 50 consecutive days.

Impressive, right?

Of course, it is.

But that wasn’t enough for James. So earlier this year, he embarked on Conquer One Hundred -- 100 FULL-DISTANCE TRIATHLONS IN 100 CONSECUTIVE DAYS. That’s 140.6 miles a day for 14 weeks, totaling 14,060 miles.

Absolutely MIIND-BOGGLING!

Obviously, you need to be in PEAK PHYSICAL CONDITION to do this. Just as important, you have to have an unparalleled degree of MENTAL TOUGHNESS as well.

In this episode, James and I talk about the importance of PERSONAL ACCOUNTABILITY, how to OVERCOME ADVERSITY, and why setbacks and hitting rock bottom are so important as you make the journey toward your goal.

James also reveals his number one SECRET to mental toughness and SETTING GOALS, and how these things can apply to you.

And believe it or not, the first 20 of the Ironmans were harder than the rest. That’s because James understood the need to ADAPT AND EVOLVE as he approached each day, especially after he learned he had developed a STRESS FRACTURE early on in the Conquer One Hundred project.

We also have an extended discussion about being PRESENT IN THE MOMENT and breaking large tasks down into small and focused efforts.

PRO TIP: The secret to taking on 100 triathlons (or any task for that matter) is one step and one mile at a time.

This is a jam-packed and EMOTIONAL discussion about how to push yourself to new limits.

node.text:
You do NOT have to BELIEVE everything you THINK.

If you don't become aware of what you’re thinking, then all kinds of old patterns and thoughts will continue to rule your life.

THOUGHT PATTERNS of worrying, worthlessness, fear, and hundreds of other negative ingrained thoughts that don't serve you.

You don’t know why or how you got there, only that you’ve got the blues and you can’t seem to shake them.

It takes WORK to control what and how you think. 

You must be INTENTIONAL about it when you don’t pay attention and apply yourself, you let external forces make those choices for you.

Instead, you can make a CONSCIOUS decision about how to program your mind. You can decide right HERE AND NOW how you want to feel, and where you want to spend your ENERGY and TIME.

Become aware of these untrue and harmful thoughts… Just simply stop and question them and evaluate them.

IS THIS THOUGHT REALLY TRUE? 

Or is this me doing what I always do?

When you SEPARATE from the thought, it looses all of its power over you.

If you change how you approach your thinking to an ACTIVE MINDSET instead of a passive mindset, soon enough you’ll rewire your brain and controlling your thoughts will become second nature.

When you are aware of how you think, negative thoughts lose their power over you.

You have a choice on how do you want to think.

Choose WISELY.

node.text:
I don’t care who you are, how much money you have, or how successful you are.

KINDNESS COSTS NOTHING.

But it means EVERYTHING.

It takes no effort to treat everyone you meet with COMPASSION and CONSIDERATION.

Small acts of kindness can have a huge RIPPLE EFFECT on someone’s life. When you’re nice to someone, it validates them. It says they are important. It says “I care about you.”

A SMILE, a HUG, or RECOGNITION of a job well done is one of the most important GIFTS you can give others. Make it a practice to give this gift often and freely.

Also remember, how you treat other people defines who you are.

Don’t discount the fact that when you’re NICE to other people, it comes back to you many times over. Making other people feel GOOD, makes you feel good, too.

This type of KARMA is real.

I’ve seen it.

I believe in it.

And so should you.

Be NICE, always.

I guarantee you…it matters.

node.text:
When it comes down to it, there's only ONE PERSON you really need to be HONEST with...

YOU.

Your life is defined by the choices you make.

Some people choose to be the center of attention, the life of the party. But understand making that CHOICE comes at a price.

Rarely are they people of substance.

The SMART people in life understand that the GREATEST REWARDS don't come that way. They understand that to be SUCCESSFUL there are no shortcuts.

TAG A FRIEND in your inner circle who is winning WITH YOU! 👊🏾

Give careful thought to your INNER CIRCLE of friends, too.

They are also a reflection of important choices you make, and will either add significantly to your life or weigh you down with unwanted distractions.

It's EASY to find party people. But it's smarter to find those who are willing to pay the price.

Make this your way of life and I guarantee you you'll be looking back in the rearview mirror at all of those people who thought it was cooler to be cool than to WORK HARD.

GET OUT THERE and build something you can be proud of for the rest of your life.

node.text:
One way or another, the game of LIFE will find you.

And it’s up to you to decide how you want to PLAY THE GAME.

YOU need to start dictating the terms of your life, instead of ALLOWING OTHERS to dictate to you.

You either dig in and ATTACK your challenges or you respond and react (playing defense).

Nobody wins on their heels.

Life is not about preventing problems, reacting to other peoples issues and playing it safe.

We learn, grow and EXPERIENCE life by playing offense.

HOWEVER ……

If you take a laid-back approach, you give up control.

You waste GOLDEN OPPORTUNITIES to have a say in outcomes that are important to you.

When you default to playing defense, you’re always reacting.

This is a LAZY approach to life, and I guarantee you’re NEVER going to like the final score when you let others decide how the game is played.

But when you play OFFENSE...

You’re forcing somebody else to play defense.

Playing defense is part of PLAYING the game.

Playing offense is where games are WON.

That’s why winners constantly look for ways to grab the ball, run toward their goals, and become MASTERS of their own outcomes.

How are YOU going to play the game?

Are you in it to WIN it? 

Or are you settling for second place?
